Subject: [PATCH] E2E review fixups: restore the revenue chart, align profit
 composition, close F-17
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Findings from the post-remediation end-to-end review:

- E2E-1 (HIGH, introduced by the F-09 field unification): reports.html's
  monthly revenue chart still read the legacy AppState.transactionHistory,
  which the load-time normalizer now always removes — the chart rendered
  zeros. Reads the canonical AppState.transactions (the normalizer merges
  legacy records there, and the payment objects carry the same details).
- E2E-2 (MEDIUM): the dashboard's Total Profit includes penalty income;
  reports' Total Revenue did not, so the two figures diverged after the
  first late penalty. Reports now includes totalPenaltiesEarned.
- E2E-3 (LOW): settings wrote the legacy deployedCapital field back onto
  state on every settings save ('Ensure compatibility') — a zombie the
  normalizer deleted on next load; removed, along with a dead fallback read.
- E2E-4 (LOW): the add-amount adjustment hand-incremented deployed;
  arithmetically correct, but it was the last spot trusting a hand-kept
  counter — now recalculates derived totals like every other mutation.
- E2E-5 (MEDIUM, pre-existing): the Web-Share-Target 'amount' parameter
  autofilled #loanAmount, an element that does not exist (the input is
  #principal) — shared-link amounts were silently dropped. Retargeted.
- E2E-6 (LOW, F-17): clients.html logged the calculator hand-off URL
  params (client name + account number) and 5 other lines; reports.html
  logged 2 — both pages' logs now gated behind DEBUG, completing F-17.
